                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13644967" author="yukim" created="Mon, 29 Apr 2013 22:24:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to fail repair when the participants&apos; versions are different.&lt;br/&gt;
Note that we don&apos;t need to check if the node is pre-1.1 for sequential repair, I removed that check also.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13644982" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 29 Apr 2013 22:35:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would change the message to &quot;different protocol versions&quot; or &quot;different major releases&quot; since different minor releases should be okay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13645872" author="yukim" created="Tue, 30 Apr 2013 19:30:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed with the message fix. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13656634" author="yukim" created="Tue, 14 May 2013 02:02:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix was unreliable because every time connection is closed, protocol version for that connection is also reset (set to null), leading to not able to repair randomly.&lt;br/&gt;
Reverted from 1.2 branch and trunk for now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13727275" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 2 Aug 2013 03:28:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wontfixing since we should be able to do cross-version repair in 2.0.  Please reopen if I&apos;ve misunderstood.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
